\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces The Preservation Paradox: the dominant zoning classification of Oahu golf land. Each tile represents 1\% of the total Oahu golf footprint, sized by land-area share. The Grand Mean total Oahu opportunity cost of \$28.6B decomposes by zoning class as approximately \$23.4B in Preservation/Federal zones (legally restricted), \$3.9B in Agriculture zones, and \$1.3B in Resort/Residential/Other zones (legally permitted under most current zoning).}}{24}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:preservation_paradox}{{8}{24}{The Preservation Paradox: the dominant zoning classification of Oahu golf land. Each tile represents 1\% of the total Oahu golf footprint, sized by land-area share. The Grand Mean total Oahu opportunity cost of \$28.6B decomposes by zoning class as approximately \$23.4B in Preservation/Federal zones (legally restricted), \$3.9B in Agriculture zones, and \$1.3B in Resort/Residential/Other zones (legally permitted under most current zoning)}{figure.caption.13}{}}
